    • Method Detail

      • findPoByNativeId

        <P extends DecoratedPersistenceObject> P findPoByNativeId(long nativeDbId)
        Find a persistence object which is backed by the database object with the given native identity.

        Note that great care must be taken when using this method depending on the database being used. It is possible that native identities are re-used in some databases and so the object you are looking for may not be the one corresponding to this identity. Additional validation mechanisms should be used to detect such a scenario.

        Type Parameters:
        P - the type of object being found. Sub-class of DecoratedPersistenceObject
        Parameters:
        nativeDbId - native database ID of the object in the database representing the persistence object to search for.
        Returns:
        the persistence object backed by the database object with the supplied ID, or null if no such persistent object exists (which includes the case where the supplied database identity is not used to store something representing a persistence object.

      • findPosByIds

        java.util.List<DecoratedPersistenceObject> findPosByIds(java.util.List<java.lang.Long> ids)
        Find persistence objects with the given identities.
        Parameters:
        ids - unique IDs of the persistence objects to search for. POs are returned in the order they were requested. No entry will be returned for any duplicate or invalid IDs.
        Returns:
